---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Pivotal Web Services PWS
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Create account
https://run.pivotal.io
- credentials (chrome)

# Organization & Space
- Org: ttt-org
- by default, it creates the space (named development) where you will work


# Tutorial:
https://pivotal.io/platform/pcf-tutorials/getting-started-with-pivotal-cloud-foundry

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Cloud Foundry CLI
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Install
    $ brew update
    $ brew tap cloudfoundry/tap
    $ brew install cf-cli

    $ cf --version

# Login to PWS/PAS
    $ cf login -a api.run.pivotal.io

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Deploy todoapp to PAS
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ cf push <name-of-the-app> -p <location of jar> -n <unique subdomain>

Example:
$ cf push TodoApp -p /Users/ttt/dev/workspaces/prospringboot2/ch12-spring-cloud/todo-cloud-microservice/target/todo-cloud-microservice-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar -n ttt-todo-app

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
View Logs
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- Logs Tab
or
- $ cf logs TodoApp

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Test the app
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
$ curl -XPOST -d '{"description":"Learn to play Guitar"}' -H "Content-Type: application/json" https://ttt-todo-app.cfapps.io/api/todos